%I A072249 #21 Jun 22 2026 22:53:16
%S A072249 5,7,11,17,21,27,35,41
%N A072249 a(n) is the least k such that for every m >= k, the characteristic set of the lollipop graph C_{m,n} is the central edge of its pendant path.
%C A072249 From _Bartlomiej Pawlik_, Jun 17 2026: (Start)
%C A072249 The lollipop graph C_{m,n} is the unicyclic graph on m vertices obtained by joining a cycle of length n to an endpoint of a path on m-n+1 vertices.
%C A072249 The characteristic set of a graph with respect to a Fiedler vector consists of the vertices at which the vector is zero and the edges whose endpoints have values of opposite signs.
%C A072249 More precisely, a(n) is the least k such that, for every m >= k, the characteristic set of C_{m,n}, labeled as in Fig. 9 of Fallat, Kirkland and Pati, is the single edge [ceiling(m/2), ceiling(m/2)+1]. (End)
%H A072249 S. M. Fallat, S. Kirkland and S. Pati, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0012-365X(01)00355-7">Minimizing algebraic connectivity over connected graphs with fixed girth</a>, Discr. Math., 254 (2002), 115-142.
%F A072249 a(n) <= floor((-3 + sqrt(16*Pi^2*n*(n - 1)^2 + 10))/8) + 1. - _Bartlomiej Pawlik_, Jun 17 2026
%K A072249 nonn,more,changed
